ATTENTION 4TH GRADE PARENTS & GUARDIANS!!! If you would like to participate in the 4th grade Clap Out Video, please send the following to mccorkle.timothy@byramschools.org :

1) Your child's name
2) 1-2 pictures of your child
3) a brief message to be displayed (Congrats, So proud of you, Good luck in 5th, etc.)

All pictures and messages need to be received no later than Monday, June 8th.

For anyone who does not send pictures and a message in, I will pull your child's yearbook photo and include that picture in the montage. I am looking to have the video published and shared out to you, the students and staff as early as Friday, June 12, but no later than Monday June 15th.

Thank you for your help with this as we make the best of our current situation and provide a closing experience for our 4th grade students! Please let us know if you have any questions and I will do my best to help!

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,

During his press conference held last Thursday, April 16, 2020, Governor Murphy announced that all NJ schools will remain closed through Friday, May 15, 2020. In an effort to provide clear and concise guidance to the members of our school community, please be advised that at this time the Byram Township Schools will be extending the school closure through 5/15/20. All school activities will be cancelled through 5/15/20.

Remote learning plans will remain in effect throughout the duration of this closure. We will continue to reevaluate and assess the situation based upon current information and directives from Governor Murphy, the New Jersey Department of Education, and the New Jersey Department of Health on a weekly basis. Additional information will be shared with our community as it becomes available.

Thank you for your continued support as we implement remote learning plans for all students. Please reach out to the school with any questions or concerns.



Sincerely,

Bryan Hensz
